					<head>Pentateuch and Prophets</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420" rend="visible">
						<summary>Pentateuch and the Former Prophets, provided with vowel-points and accents. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420, lccn.loc.gov/n80008482">
							<locus from="1r" to="215v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Torah u-neviʼim rishonim</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">תורה ונביאים ראשונים</title>
							<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
							<note>
								<p>The masoretic notes are very scanty, being almost entirely confined to the מלא and חסר, and כתיב and קרי.</p>
								<p>The two verses which are omitted in the printed text of the Bible after Joshua 21:35 are contained in this manuscript. with a marginal note: <q>אלו שני הפסוקים אינם כתובים בהללי ולא בספר בבלי</q> (written in the same hand as the owner's note on folio 2r).   </p>
							</note>
							<msItem rend="visible">
								<locus from="1r" to="14v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Genesis</title>
								<note>
									<p>Missing chapters 1:1-29:7 and 37:23-39:5.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="visible">
								<locus from="14v" to="42r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en" rend="visible">Exodus</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="visible">
								<locus from="42r" to="60r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Leviticus</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="visible">
								<locus from="60r" to="86r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Numbers</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="visible">
								<locus from="86r" to="108v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Deuteronomy</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="visible">
								<locus from="108v" to="124v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Joshua</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="visible">
								<locus from="124v" to="140r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Judges</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="visible">
								<locus from="140r" to="178r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Samuel</title>
								<note>
									<p>2Samuel starts on folio160v.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="visible">
								<locus from="178r" to="215v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Kings</title>
								<note>
									<p>Missing chapters 16:15-17:34 and 25:22-30.</p>
									<p>2Kings starts on folio 198r.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Vellum codex of probably 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>215 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>198</height>
										<width>152</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>215 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning of the manuscript, 1 after folio 5, 1 after folio 208 and 2 at the end of the manuscript).  </p>
									<p>The Hebrew foliation shows that the first extant leaf was originally the 17th.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>27 extant quires mostly of 8 leaves, but the codex is missing 16 pages at the beginning and several pages throughout the manuscript.</p>
									<p>Quires are marked with catchwords on the last page of the quire.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>A number of leaves are missing, folios 41 and 115 are mutilated.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="25" writtenLines="25">
									<p>Ruling with hard point, pricking is not currently visible.</p>
									<p>Several lacunae.</p>
									<p>The books of Leviticus (42r) and Kings (178r) begin a new leaf, and between the other books there is a blank of four lines.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi semi-cursive script with supralinear punctuation, probably of the 14th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<decoDesc>
							<summary>1 half-border on page 108v.</summary>
							<decoNote type="border">A one-column border, in colour.<locus n="108v"/>
							</decoNote>
						</decoDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Marginal note of the owner on folio 122r.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person">Musa ibn Sulaiman ʻIraḳi</name>, inscribed with his name on folio 2r, attesting that the manuscript is a property of ʻImrān: מוסי אבן סלימאן עראקי יצו' אן אלכתאב חק עמראן יצו'.</p>
						</additions>
